                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-02-25</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>This was one book that I could not put down.  The book is broken into large sections, each dealing with a particular criminal and his corresponding activities.  In-depth descriptions of what was going on behind the scenes at some of the most respected financial firms of the time--absolutely fascinating.  If you were around in the 80's, and you work/participate in the investment industry, this should be required historical reading.</span>
                  
              
